info.title: The Farmers Arms
info.address: 71 Chapel Ln, Wilmslow SK9 5JH, United Kingdom

data.text: Best pub in Wilmslow by a country mile
data.name: Mike Walsh

data.text: This is a proper pub, with decent genuine customers.  If you're a poser or a wannabe.....this is not the place for you.  Good old fashioned no nonsense landlord which is a breath of fresh air.  Well run and chilled atmosphere.  A place you can you go feeling a bit scruffy after dog walking and nobody will bat an eye lid.  Good ale and wine .
data.name: S

data.text: Went here for my brother's 70th birthday. Fantastic night you know you have had a good night, when you tummy and cheeks are aching through laughing.
data.name: Shirley Bartholomew

data.text: It's a proper pub and great banter & characters that go all the way for you.. recommended ..

data.text:
Great 'local' friendly pub. Not for the Cheshire set, just an honest fun place.
Doing a lot with the chapel lane community with seasonal markets and events. What can I say more. I work with them regularly and they are a great community pub a real focal point. Courtney and John are fantastic.
